postcontent:
Springfield SAR-8 (Greek Manufactured HK91), .308 Win./7.62 NATO, excellant condition. Made in Greece under HK license and SA contract. Steel (not aluminum) receiver. Comes with several mags and extra 1 piece stock. Add $500 for Leopold 2.5-8x40 scope made for .308.

Tech. Specs: caliber- .308 Win./ 7.62 NATO, operating system-roller block delay, Barrel- hammer forged, Rifling- 4 groove, 1 in 11, barrel length-18in. Anyone familiar with the SAR-8 is aware that this rifle was manufactured as a licensed copy of the HK91/93, made on HK tooling with HK technical assistance given to Helenic Arms of Greece. As Mark Christian stated, "These rifles are not clones, they are the real thing". 

Years ago HK set up a Greek company(Hellenic Arms) with HK tooling and HK trained techs to make HK91's.These were imported by Springfield Armory as SAR3's.When the 89 ban hit the ones that were in the process of being imported were restamped SAR8's––these are called overstamps.SAR3's and SAR8 overstamps are equal to true HK91's in most everybodys opinion.
